# Kenku FM Remote API

## Registration

Routes register in `src/main/remote/index.ts` via `registerRemote(manager)`. Server starts in `PlayerManager.startRemote(address, port)`.

## Route pattern

```typescript
// 1. Fastify route in src/main/remote/routes/
const view = manager.getView();
if (view) {
  view.send("PLAYER_REMOTE_SOMETHING", payload);
  reply.status(200).send(result);
} else {
  reply.status(503).send(VIEW_ERROR);
}

// 2. Player preload handles PLAYER_REMOTE_* and replies via ipcMain
```

## Types

Shared reply types live in `src/types/player.ts`. Request/response schemas use `@sinclair/typebox` in route files.

## Adding a new endpoint

1. Create route file under `src/main/remote/routes/`
2. Register in `src/main/remote/index.ts` with `/v1/` prefix
3. Add `PLAYER_REMOTE_*` handler in player preload or `*Remote.tsx` component
4. Add types to `src/types/player.ts` if needed
5. Keep `/v1/` prefix stable — Stream Deck plugin depends on it

## Errors

- `VIEW_ERROR` (503): player BrowserView not registered
- Reply timeout: 5 seconds on `*_REPLY` IPC pairs
